FBIS4-9800 "drlat064_c_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-064 Daily Report 31 Mar 1994 MEXICO Two Offices Inaugurated Within NAFTA Framework Two Offices Inaugurated Within NAFTA Framework PA0204191094 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 0430 GMT 31 Mar 94 PA0204191094 Mexico City XEW Television Network Spanish BFN [From the "24 Hours" newscast] [Text] The main offices of two new institutions were announced today within the framework of NAFTA. The headquarters of the North American Development Bank will be located in San Antonio, Texas, and the Environmental Cooperation Border Commission will be headquartered in Ciudad Juarez, Chihuahua State. During the first two months of this year, foreign investment in Mexico rose to more than $4 billion, which is 143 percent higher than the figure registered during the same period in 1993, the Commerce and Industrial Development Secretariat announced.
